### Get Installed Screen by Name or Object

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Retrieves an installed screen either by its name (string) or by a Screen object. An optional `screen_class` parameter can be provided to filter by expected screen type. Raises `KeyError` if the screen is not found.

```python
get_screen(screen: ScreenType) -> ScreenType
```

```python
get_screen(screen: str) -> Screen
```

```python
get_screen(
    screen: str,
    screen_class: Type[ScreenType] | None = None,
) -> ScreenType
```

```python
get_screen(
    screen: ScreenType,
    screen_class: Type[ScreenType] | None = None,
) -> ScreenType
```

```python
get_screen(screen, screen_class=None)
```

