### Install Screen

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Installs a screen, ensuring it is not destroyed when removed from the screen stack. This function is used to manage persistent screens within the application. Note that installing a screen does not make it active; use `push_screen` or `switch_screen` for that purpose. It returns an awaitable that completes once the screen and its children are mounted.

```python
install_screen(screen, name)
```

