### Textualize.io Position Example (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/position

Demonstrates how to set the 'position' style for widgets in a Textualize.io application using Python. This example shows how to create two labels with different positioning.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Label


class PositionApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "position.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Label("Absolute", id="label1")
        yield Label("Relative", id="label2")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = PositionApp()
    app.run()

```

