### GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/is_screen_installed

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Verifies if a specific screen, identified by its object or name, has been installed in the Textual application.

```APIDOC
## GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/is_screen_installed

### Description
Checks if a given screen has been installed.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
`/websites/textual_textualize_io/is_screen_installed`

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **screen** (Screen | str) - Required - Either a Screen object or screen name (the `name` argument when installed).

### Request Example
```json
{
  "screen": "screen_name_or_object"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **installed** (bool) - True if the screen is currently installed.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "installed": true
}
```
```

