### GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/get_screen

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Retrieves an installed screen by its name or object. An optional screen class can be provided to filter the search. Raises KeyError if the screen is not found.

```APIDOC
## GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/get_screen

### Description
Get an installed screen. This method can accept either a Screen object or a screen name. You can also specify an expected screen class to filter the results.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/get_screen

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **screen** (Screen | str) - Required - Either a Screen object or the screen name.
- **screen_class** (Type[Screen] | None) - Optional - The class of the expected screen. Defaults to None (any screen class).

### Request Body
None

### Request Example
```json
{
  "screen": "settings",
  "screen_class": "MySettingsScreen"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **Screen** - A screen instance.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "screen_name": "settings",
  "layout": "vertical"
}
```

#### Error Response (404)
- **KeyError** - If the named screen doesn't exist.

#### Error Response Example
```json
{
  "error": "Screen 'non_existent_screen' not found."
}
```
```

