### POST /websites/textual_textualize_io/install_screen

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Installs a screen, preventing Textual from destroying it when it's no longer on the screen stack. Does not make the screen current.

```APIDOC
## POST /websites/textual_textualize_io/install_screen

### Description
Installs a screen. Installing a screen prevents Textual from destroying it when it is no longer on the screen stack. Note that you don't need to install a screen to use it. See push_screen or switch_screen to make a new screen current.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
`/websites/textual_textualize_io/install_screen`

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **screen** (Screen) - Required - Screen to install.
- **name** (str) - Required - Unique name to identify the screen.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "screen": "<screen_object_representation>",
  "name": "my_screen_name"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **message** (string) - Confirmation message indicating the screen installation.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "message": "Screen 'my_screen_name' installed successfully."
}
```

#### Error Response
- **ScreenError** - If the screen can't be installed.
```

