### Header with App Title and Sub-title (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/header

This example illustrates how to set the application's title and sub-title, which are then displayed by the Header widget. It extends the basic Header example by defining `self.title` and `self.sub_title` in the `on_mount` method.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Header


class HeaderApp(App):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Header()

    def on_mount(self) -> None:
        self.title = "Header Application"
        self.sub_title = "With title and sub-title"


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = HeaderApp()
    app.run()

```

