### GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/get_default_screen

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Gets the default screen instance that is used when the App is first composed. Subclasses can implement this to provide a custom default screen.

```APIDOC
## GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/get_default_screen

### Description
Get the default screen. This is called when the App is first composed. The returned screen instance will be the first screen on the stack. Implement this method if you would like to use a custom Screen as the default screen.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/get_default_screen

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
None

### Request Body
None

### Request Example
```json
{}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **Screen** - A screen instance.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "screen_name": "default_screen",
  "widget_count": 5
}
```
```

