### Placeholder Widget Example in Python

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/blog/2022/12/11/version-060

This Python code demonstrates how to use the Placeholder widget within a Textual application. It showcases different ways to instantiate the widget, including custom labels, IDs, and variants like 'size' and 'text'. The example utilizes Textual's layout containers to arrange multiple placeholders.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Container, Horizontal, VerticalScroll
from textual.widgets import Placeholder


class PlaceholderApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "placeholder.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield VerticalScroll(
            Container(
                Placeholder("This is a custom label for p1.", id="p1"),
                Placeholder("Placeholder p2 here!", id="p2"),
                Placeholder(id="p3"),
                Placeholder(id="p4"),
                Placeholder(id="p5"),
                Placeholder(),
                Horizontal(
                    Placeholder(variant="size", id="col1"),
                    Placeholder(variant="text", id="col2"),
                    Placeholder(variant="size", id="col3"),
                    id="c1",
                ),
                id="bot",
            ),
            Container(
                Placeholder(variant="text", id="left"),
                Placeholder(variant="size", id="topright"),
                Placeholder(variant="text", id="botright"),
                id="top",
            ),
            id="content",
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = PlaceholderApp()
    app.run()

```

