### Initialize LLM Model on App Mount

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/blog/2024/09/15/anatomy-of-a-textual-user-interface

This method is triggered when the Textual app mounts, typically used for initial setup. It loads a specified LLM model (e.g., 'gpt-4o') using the `llm` library. The chosen model can be replaced with any other supported model.

```python
def on_mount(self) -> None:
    self.model = llm.get_model("gpt-4o")
```

