### Textual CSS with Dynamic '.started' Class

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/tutorial

This CSS snippet introduces dynamic styling using a CSS class named '.started'. It defines styles that apply only when a widget has this class, such as changing the background and text color, and controlling the display of start/stop buttons and the visibility of the reset button.

```css
.started {
    background: $success-muted;
    color: $text;
}

.started TimeDisplay {
    color: $foreground;
}

.started #start {
    display: none
}

.started #stop {
    display: block
}

.started #reset {
    visibility: hidden
}


```

