### Run App API

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Starts and runs the Textual application. Supports various modes including headless, inline display, and mouse event handling.

```APIDOC
## POST /run

### Description
Run the app.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/run

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **headless** (bool) - Optional - Run in headless mode (no output). Defaults to `False`.
- **inline** (bool) - Optional - Run the app inline (under the prompt). Defaults to `False`.
- **inline_no_clear** (bool) - Optional - Don't clear the app output when exiting an inline app. Defaults to `False`.
- **mouse** (bool) - Optional - Enable mouse support. Defaults to `True`.
- **size** (tuple[int, int] | None) - Optional - Force terminal size to `(WIDTH, HEIGHT)`, or None to auto-detect. Defaults to `None`.
- **auto_pilot** (AutopilotCallbackType | None) - Optional - An auto pilot coroutine. Defaults to `None`.
- **loop** (AbstractEventLoop | None) - Optional - Asyncio loop instance, or `None` to use default. Defaults to `None`.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **message** (string) - Indicates the app has finished running.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "message": "App finished running."
}
```
```

