### Python App with Link-Style Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/links/link_style

A complete Textual application demonstrating the use of the link-style CSS property. It includes labels with both regular hyperlinks and action links, showcasing how link-style only affects the latter.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Label


class LinkStyleApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "link_style.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Label(
            "Visit the [link='https://textualize.io']Textualize[/link] website.",
            id="lbl1",
        )
        yield Label(
            "Click [@click=app.bell]here[/] for the bell sound.",
            id="lbl2",
        )
        yield Label(
            "You can also click [@click=app.bell]here[/] for the bell sound.",
            id="lbl3",
        )
        yield Label(
            "[@click=app.quit]Exit this application.[/]",
            id="lbl4",
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = LinkStyleApp()
    app.run()

```

