### Textual App with Header and Footer Widgets

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/CSS

This example extends the basic Textual app by composing `Header` and `Footer` widgets. These widgets are added as children to the `Screen`, creating more branches in the DOM tree. This showcases how to include common UI elements that contribute to the application's structure.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Header, Footer


class ExampleApp(App):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Header()
        yield Footer()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ExampleApp()
    app.run()

```

