### Non-Nested CSS Stylesheet Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/CSS

This example shows a traditional, non-nested CSS stylesheet for styling a container, buttons, and specific button states (affirmative and negative). It lacks grouping and repeats the parent selector.

```tcss
/* Style the container */
#questions {
    border: heavy $primary;
    align: center middle;
}

/* Style all buttons */
#questions .button {
    width: 1fr;
    padding: 1 2;
    margin: 1 2;
    text-align: center;
    border: heavy $panel;
}

/* Style the Yes button */
#questions .button.affirmative {
    border: heavy $success;
}

/* Style the No button */
#questions .button.negative {
    border: heavy $error;
}

```

