### Configuring Project Metadata and Dependencies in pyproject.toml

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/how-to/package-with-hatch

Shows how to define project metadata, including name, description, and author information, and crucially, how to specify project dependencies within the `[project]` section of `pyproject.toml`. This ensures required libraries are installed with the application.

```toml
[project]
name = "textual-calculator"
dynamic = ["version"]
description = 'A example app'
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.8"
license = "MIT"
keywords = []
authors = [
  { name = "Will McGugan", email = "redacted@textualize.io" },
]
classifiers = [
  "Development Status :: 4 - Beta",
  "Programming Language :: Python",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython",
  "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy",
]
dependencies = []

```

