### Python Textual ListView Control Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/blog/2022/12/11/version-060

Illustrates the implementation of the new Textual ListView widget, which enables navigation and selection of items within a list. Each list item can be a widget, facilitating the creation of complex controls. The example includes CSS for styling.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Footer, Label, ListItem, ListView


class ListViewExample(App):
    CSS_PATH = "list_view.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield ListView(
            ListItem(Label("One")),
            ListItem(Label("Two")),
            ListItem(Label("Three")),
        )
        yield Footer()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ListViewExample()
    app.run()

```

