### Syntax Highlighting Query Example (Tree-sitter)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

This snippet shows a simplified tree-sitter highlight query for Markdown. It maps specific syntax nodes identified by the parser (e.g., 'heading_content', 'link') to highlight names ('@heading', '@link'). These names are then used to apply styles within a Textual TextAreaTheme.

```tree-sitter query
(heading_content) @heading
(link) @link

```

