### Textual App with Content Markup Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/content

Demonstrates how to use Textual's content markup to style text within Static widgets. It shows the difference between enabling and disabling markup, and how tags affect the displayed text. Includes basic app structure, CSS, and widget composition.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static

TEXT1 = """
Hello, [bold $text on $primary]World[/]!

[@click=app.notify('Hello, World!')]Click me[/]
"""

TEXT2 = """
Maki will [bold]not[/bold] be displayed.

Tags will be left in the output.

"""


class ContentApp(App):
    CSS = """
    Screen {
        Static {
            height: 1fr;
        }
        #text1 { background: $primary-muted; }
        #text2 { background: $error-muted; }
    }
    """

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static(TEXT1, id="text1")
        yield Static(TEXT2, id="text2", markup=False)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ContentApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### App uninstall_screen(screen)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Uninstalls a screen from the application. If the screen was not installed, this is a no-op.

```APIDOC
## uninstall_screen(screen)

### Description
Uninstall a screen. If the screen was not previously installed, then this method is a null-op. Uninstalling a screen allows Textual to delete it when it is popped or switched. Note that uninstalling a screen is only required if you have previously installed it with install_screen. Textual will also uninstall screens automatically on exit.

### Method
`uninstall_screen(screen)`

### Endpoint
N/A (Method within a class)

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
- **screen** (Screen | str) - Required - The screen to uninstall or the name of an installed screen.

### Request Example
```python
app.uninstall_screen("my_screen_name")
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **str | None** - The name of the screen that was uninstalled, or None if no screen was uninstalled.

#### Response Example
```
"my_screen_name"
```
```

