### App switch_mode(mode)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Switches the application to a specified mode, optionally awaiting the associated screen to mount.

```APIDOC
## switch_mode(mode)

### Description
Switch to a given mode.

### Method
`switch_mode(mode)`

### Endpoint
N/A (Method within a class)

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
- **mode** (str) - Required - The mode to switch to.

### Request Example
```python
app.switch_mode("my_mode")
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **AwaitMount** (Awaitable) - An optionally awaitable object which waits for the screen associated with the mode to be mounted.

#### Response Example
```python
await app.switch_mode("my_mode")
```

### Raises
- `UnknownModeError`: If trying to switch to an unknown mode.
```

