### Textual - Python Example for Text Wrapping

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/text_wrap

Demonstrates the usage of text-wrap in Textual applications using Python. It showcases how to apply 'wrap' and 'nowrap' styles to Static widgets to control text wrapping behavior.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static

TEXT = """I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. I will face my fear."""


class WrapApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "text_wrap.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static(TEXT, id="static1")
        yield Static(TEXT, id="static2")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = WrapApp()
    app.run()

```

