### Selection Class

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

The `Selection` class represents a range of characters within a document, defined by a start and end point. It provides utility methods to check if a selection is empty (i.e., a cursor) and to create a cursor at a specific location. The selection is inclusive of the start point and exclusive of the end point.

```Python
Selection.cursor(location)
```

```Python
is_empty
```

```Python
start = (0, 0)
```

```Python
end = (0, 0)
```

