### Textual Color Class Initialization and Example Usage

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/color

Demonstrates the initialization and basic usage of the Color class, including parsing color strings, basic arithmetic operations, and creating colors with alpha values.

```python
>>> from textual.color import Color
>>> color = Color.parse("red")
>>> color
Color(255, 0, 0)
>>> color.darken(0.5)
Color(98, 0, 0)
>>> color + Color.parse("green")
Color(0, 128, 0)
>>> color_with_alpha = Color(100, 50, 25, 0.5)
>>> color_with_alpha
Color(100, 50, 25, a=0.5)
>>> color + color_with_alpha
Color(177, 25, 12)
```

