### Create a Simple Textual App for Testing (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/testing

This Python code defines a Textual application with three buttons (Red, Green, Blue) and keyboard shortcuts to change the background color. It includes CSS for basic styling and bindings for keyboard actions. This app serves as a target for testing user interface interactions.

```Python
from textual import on
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Horizontal
from textual.widgets import Button, Footer


class RGBApp(App):
    CSS = """
    Screen {
        align: center middle;
    }
    Horizontal {
        width: auto;
        height: auto;
    }
    """

    BINDINGS = [
        ("r", "switch_color('red')", "Go Red"),
        ("g", "switch_color('green')", "Go Green"),
        ("b", "switch_color('blue')", "Go Blue"),
    ]

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        with Horizontal():
            yield Button("Red", id="red")
            yield Button("Green", id="green")
            yield Button("Blue", id="blue")
        yield Footer()

    @on(Button.Pressed)
    def pressed_button(self, event: Button.Pressed) -> None:
        assert event.button.id is not None
        self.action_switch_color(event.button.id)

    def action_switch_color(self, color: str) -> None:
        self.screen.styles.background = color


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = RGBApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### Center Widgets in Textual App

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/FAQ

Demonstrates how to center widgets within a Textual application screen using CSS 'align' property and the 'Center' container. The first example shows default alignment, while the second illustrates effective centering with multiple widgets.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Button

class ButtonApp(App):

    CSS = """
    Screen {
        align: center middle;
    }
    """

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Button("PUSH ME!")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    ButtonApp().run()
```

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Center
from textual.widgets import Button

class ButtonApp(App):

    CSS = """
    Screen {
        align: center middle;
    }
    """

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Center(Button("PUSH ME!"))
        yield Center(Button("AND ME!"))
        yield Center(Button("ALSO PLEASE PUSH ME!"))
        yield Center(Button("HEY ME ALSO!!"))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    ButtonApp().run()
```

