### Textual App with min-width Examples (Python & CSS)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/min_width

Demonstrates setting minimum widths for Placeholder widgets using both Python and CSS. The Python code defines the app structure and links to the CSS file, while the CSS file applies different min-width values to individual placeholders.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.containers import VerticalScroll
from textual.widgets import Placeholder


class MinWidthApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "min_width.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield VerticalScroll(
            Placeholder("min-width: 25%", id="p1"),
            Placeholder("min-width: 75%", id="p2"),
            Placeholder("min-width: 100", id="p3"),
            Placeholder("min-width: 400h", id="p4"),
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = MinWidthApp()
    app.run()

```

```css
VerticalScroll {
    height: 100%;
    width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
}

Placeholder {
    height: 1fr;
    width: 50%;
}

#p1 {
    min-width: 25%;

}

#p2 {
    min-width: 75%;
}

#p3 {
    min-width: 100;
}

#p4 {
    min-width: 400h;
}


```

