### Cache Management API

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/cache

This section details the methods available for managing the cache, such as setting, getting, and clearing entries.

```APIDOC
## GET /cache

### Description
Retrieves the current state of the cache, including its keys and potentially values.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/cache

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **key** (CacheKey) - Optional - The specific key to retrieve from the cache.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **keys** (Array[CacheKey]) - A list of all keys currently in the cache.
- **values** (Object) - An object where keys are CacheKey and values are CacheValue, representing the cached items.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "keys": ["user:123", "product:456"],
  "values": {
    "user:123": {"name": "John Doe", "email": "john.doe@example.com"},
    "product:456": {"name": "Laptop", "price": 1200}
  }
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## POST /cache/set

### Description
Sets a key-value pair in the cache.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/cache/set

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **key** (CacheKey) - Required - The key to set in the cache.
- **value** (CacheValue) - Required - The value to associate with the key.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "key": "user:123",
  "value": {"name": "Jane Doe", "email": "jane.doe@example.com"}
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates if the operation was successful.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## GET /cache/get

### Description
Retrieves a value from the cache using its key. Returns a default value if the key is not found.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/cache/get

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **key** (CacheKey) - Required - The key of the item to retrieve.
- **default** (DefaultValue) - Optional - The value to return if the key is not found. Defaults to None.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **value** (CacheValue | DefaultValue | None) - The retrieved value or the default value.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "value": {"name": "John Doe", "email": "john.doe@example.com"}
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## DELETE /cache/discard

### Description
Discards an item from the cache using its key.

### Method
DELETE

### Endpoint
/cache/discard

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **key** (CacheKey) - Required - The key of the item to discard.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates if the operation was successful.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## POST /cache/clear

### Description
Clears all items from the cache.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/cache/clear

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates if the operation was successful.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## PUT /cache/maxsize

### Description
Sets or updates the maximum size of the cache. Items exceeding this size will be discarded.

### Method
PUT

### Endpoint
/cache/maxsize

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **maxsize** (int) - Required - The new maximum size for the cache.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "maxsize": 1000
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates if the operation was successful.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```
```

```APIDOC
## PUT /cache/grow

### Description
Increases the maximum size of the cache to at least the specified number of elements.

### Method
PUT

### Endpoint
/cache/grow

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **maxsize** (int) - Required - The minimum new maximum size for the cache.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "maxsize": 1500
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates if the operation was successful.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```
```

