### All Text Styles and Combinations in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/text_style

Illustrates the application of all available text styles (none, bold, italic, reverse, strike, underline) and their combinations within Textual widgets. This example uses a Grid container to display multiple labels with different styles.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.containers import Grid
from textual.widgets import Label

TEXT = """I must not fear.
Fear is the mind-killer.
Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration.
I will face my fear.
I will permit it to pass over me and through me.
And when it has gone past, I will turn the inner eye to see its path.
Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain."""


class AllTextStyleApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "text_style_all.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Grid(
            Label("none\n" + TEXT, id="lbl1"),
            Label("bold\n" + TEXT, id="lbl2"),
            Label("italic\n" + TEXT, id="lbl3"),
            Label("reverse\n" + TEXT, id="lbl4"),
            Label("strike\n" + TEXT, id="lbl5"),
            Label("underline\n" + TEXT, id="lbl6"),
            Label("bold italic\n" + TEXT, id="lbl7"),
            Label("reverse strike\n" + TEXT, id="lbl8"),
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = AllTextStyleApp()
    app.run()

```

```css
#lbl1 {
    text-style: none;
}

#lbl2 {
    text-style: bold;
}

#lbl3 {
    text-style: italic;
}

#lbl4 {
    text-style: reverse;
}

#lbl5 {
    text-style: strike;
}

#lbl6 {
    text-style: underline;
}

#lbl7 {
    text-style: bold italic;
}

#lbl8 {
    text-style: reverse strike;
}

Grid {
    grid-size: 4;
    grid-gutter: 1 2;
    margin: 1 2;
    height: 100%;
}

Label {
    height: 100%;
}

```

