### Create a TextAreaTheme Instance

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

Illustrates the basic instantiation of a TextAreaTheme object, specifying its name and optionally configuring various style attributes like base style, cursor style, and syntax styles.

```python
from textual.widgets import TextAreaTheme
from textual.style import Style

# Create a basic theme with a name
my_theme = TextAreaTheme('my_custom_theme')

# Create a theme with custom styles
styled_theme = TextAreaTheme(
    'styled_theme',
    base_style=Style(bgcolor='#222222', color='white'),
    cursor_style=Style(color='black', bgcolor='yellow'),
    selection_style=Style(bgcolor='blue'),
    syntax_styles={'keyword': Style(color='red', bold=True)}
)

```

