### Example Textual App with CSS Path

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/CSS

Demonstrates how to set a CSS file for a Textual application. The `CSS_PATH` class variable is used to specify the path to the Textual CSS file (`.tcss`) which styles the application's widgets.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Container, Horizontal
from textual.widgets import Button, Footer, Header, Static

QUESTION = "Do you want to learn about Textual CSS?"


class ExampleApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "dom4.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Header()
        yield Footer()
        yield Container(
            Static(QUESTION, classes="question"),
            Horizontal(
                Button("Yes", variant="success"),
                Button("No", variant="error"),
                classes="buttons",
            ),
            id="dialog",
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ExampleApp()
    app.run()

```

