### Register and Apply a Custom Textual TextArea Theme

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

This snippet illustrates the process of registering a custom theme with a TextArea instance and then applying it. Registration makes the theme available in the `available_themes` set, and setting the `theme` attribute switches the TextArea's appearance to the chosen theme.

```python
from textual.widgets.text_area import TextArea

text_area = TextArea()
my_theme = TextAreaTheme(name="my_cool_theme") # Assuming my_theme is defined elsewhere

text_area.register_theme(my_theme)

print(text_area.available_themes)

text_area.theme = "my_cool_theme"
```

