### Suspend App Process with Keybinding (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/app

This Python example defines a Textual app that can be suspended using a key combination (Ctrl+Z by default) via the `action_suspend_process` action. This is intended for Unix-like systems and will be ignored on Windows or within textual-web.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.binding import Binding
from textual.widgets import Label


class SuspendKeysApp(App[None]):

    BINDINGS = [Binding("ctrl+z", "suspend_process")]

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Label("Press Ctrl+Z to suspend!")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    SuspendKeysApp().run()
```

