### Nested Collapsible Widgets in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/collapsible

This example showcases how to create nested Collapsible widgets within a Textual application. It demonstrates setting the initial collapsed state for each level of nesting. The code defines a simple app structure with nested containers.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Collapsible, Label


class CollapsibleApp(App[None]):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        with Collapsible(collapsed=False):
            with Collapsible():
                yield Label("Hello, world.")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = CollapsibleApp()
    app.run()

```

