### Build Compose Methods with Context Managers (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/blog/2023/02/24/textual-0120-adds-syntactical-sugar-and-batch-updates

Demonstrates the new context manager syntax for building Textual compose methods, improving readability and editability compared to the older iteration-based approach. This method is preferred for its conciseness.

```python
for color_name in ColorSystem.COLOR_NAMES:
    with ColorGroup(id=f"group-{color_name}"):
        yield Label(f'"{color_name}"')
        for level in LEVELS:
            color = f"{color_name}-{level}" if level else color_name
            with ColorItem(classes=color):
                yield ColorBar(f"${color}", classes="text label")
                yield ColorBar("$text-muted", classes="muted")
                yield ColorBar("$text-disabled", classes="disabled")

```

