### Textualize IO - WrappedDocument API

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

Provides functionalities for handling wrapped documents, including getting offsets, line information, and converting between locations and offsets.

```APIDOC
## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_offsets

### Description
Gets the screen offsets for a given line index in a wrapped document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_offsets

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **line_index** (integer) - Required - The index of the line.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **offsets** (array) - An array of screen offsets for the line.

### Response Example
{
  "offsets": [0, 10, 20]
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_sections

### Description
Gets the sections for a given line index in a wrapped document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_sections

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **line_index** (integer) - Required - The index of the line.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **sections** (array) - An array of sections for the line.

### Response Example
{
  "sections": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "text": "section1"}]
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_tab_widths

### Description
Gets the tab widths for a given line index in a wrapped document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_tab_widths

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **line_index** (integer) - Required - The index of the line.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **tab_widths** (array) - An array of tab widths for the line.

### Response Example
{
  "tab_widths": [4, 8]
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_target_document_column

### Description
Gets the target document column for a given line index and x offset.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/get_target_document_column

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **line_index** (integer) - Required - The index of the line.
- **x_offset** (integer) - Required - The horizontal offset.
- **y_offset** (integer) - Required - The vertical offset.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **column** (integer) - The target document column.

### Response Example
{
  "column": 5
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/location_to_offset

### Description
Converts a location (line and column) to a document offset.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/location_to_offset

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **location** (object) - Required - The location object with `line` and `column` properties.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **offset** (integer) - The document offset.

### Response Example
{
  "offset": 100
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/offset_to_location

### Description
Converts a document offset to a location (line and column).

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/offset_to_location

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **offset** (integer) - Required - The document offset.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **location** (object) - The location object with `line` and `column` properties.

### Response Example
{
  "location": {"line": 10, "column": 5}
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/wrap

### Description
Wraps the document content based on the specified width and tab width.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/wrap

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **width** (integer) - Required - The maximum width for wrapping.
- **tab_width** (integer) - Required - The width of a tab character.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **wrapped_document** (object) - The wrapped document object.

### Response Example
{
  "wrapped_document": {}
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/wrap_range

### Description
Wraps a specific range of the document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/wrapped_document/wrap_range

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **start** (object) - Required - The starting point of the range.
- **old_end** (object) - Required - The original ending point of the range.
- **new_end** (object) - Required - The new ending point of the range after wrapping.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **wrapped_range** (object) - The wrapped range information.

### Response Example
{
  "wrapped_range": {}
}
```

