### CSS Offset Syntax Examples

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/offset

This snippet illustrates the syntax for applying offsets in Textual CSS. It shows how to set both horizontal and vertical offsets using the 'offset' property, and how to specify offsets for individual axes using 'offset-x' and 'offset-y'.

```css
/* Move the widget 8 cells in the x direction and 2 in the y direction */
offset: 8 2;

/* Move the widget 4 cells in the x direction
offset-x: 4;
/* Move the widget -3 cells in the y direction
offset-y: -3;


```

