--------------------------------

### Create and Configure a Custom TextArea Theme

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

This snippet demonstrates how to define a custom theme for the Textual TextArea widget. It includes setting basic styles for cursor and selection, and defining syntax highlighting rules by mapping tokens to Rich styles. This allows for personalized visual appearances of the text area.

```python
from textual.widgets.text_area import TextAreaTheme
from textual.style import Style

my_theme = TextAreaTheme(
    # This name will be used to refer to the theme...
    name="my_cool_theme",
    # Basic styles such as background, cursor, selection, gutter, etc...
    cursor_style=Style(color="white", bgcolor="blue"),
    cursor_line_style=Style(bgcolor="yellow"),
    # `syntax_styles` is for syntax highlighting.
    # It maps tokens parsed from the document to Rich styles.
    syntax_styles={
        "string": Style(color="red"),
        "comment": Style(color="magenta"),
    }
)
```

--------------------------------

### Exit Textual App with Return Value

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/app

Demonstrates exiting a Textual application using `App.exit()` and returning a value from the `run()` method. This example returns the `id` of the pressed button, allowing the calling script to determine user interaction.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Label, Button


class QuestionApp(App[str]):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Label("Do you love Textual?")
        yield Button("Yes", id="yes", variant="primary")
        yield Button("No", id="no", variant="error")

    def on_button_pressed(self, event: Button.Pressed) -> None:
        self.exit(event.button.id)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = QuestionApp()
    reply = app.run()
    print(reply)

```

