### Batch Updates and Lock Widgets with Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/widget

The `batch` async context manager combines widget locking and update batching in Textual. It's useful for performing multiple widget operations atomically. Use it within an `async with` block to ensure changes are batched together. Example shows removing buttons and mounting a label.

```python
async with container.batch():
    await container.remove_children(Button)
    await container.mount(Label("All buttons are gone."))
```

