--------------------------------

### Async Mount and Modify Widget in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/app

Shows how to asynchronously mount a widget and then immediately modify its child components. This avoids race conditions by ensuring the widget is fully mounted before subsequent operations, preventing `NoMatches` exceptions.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Button, Welcome


class WelcomeApp(App):
    async def on_key(self) -> None:
        await self.mount(Welcome())
        self.query_one(Button).label = "YES!"


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = WelcomeApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### Python: Set Grid Columns with Fractional Units

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/layout

Demonstrates how to set the width of grid columns using fractional units (fr) in Textual. This example creates a 3-column grid where the first column is twice the width of the others.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static


class GridLayoutExample(App):
    CSS_PATH = "grid_layout3_row_col_adjust.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static("One", classes="box")
        yield Static("Two", classes="box")
        yield Static("Three", classes="box")
        yield Static("Four", classes="box")
        yield Static("Five", classes="box")
        yield Static("Six", classes="box")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = GridLayoutExample()
    app.run()

```

```tcss
Screen {
    layout: grid;
    grid-size: 3;
    grid-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr;
}

.box {
    height: 100%;
    border: solid green;
}


```

