### MaskedInput Example in Python

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/masked_input

Demonstrates how to use the MaskedInput widget to create a masked input field for a credit card number. It shows custom CSS styling for valid and invalid states and how to define a template mask.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Label, MaskedInput


class MaskedInputApp(App):

    CSS = """
    MaskedInput.-valid {
        border: tall $success 60%;
    }
    MaskedInput.-valid:focus {
        border: tall $success;
    }
    MaskedInput {
        margin: 1 1;
    }
    Label {
        margin: 1 2;
    }
    """

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Label("Enter a valid credit card number.")
        yield MaskedInput(
            template="9999-9999-9999-9999;0",
        )


app = MaskedInputApp()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()

```

