--------------------------------

### Textual Sparkline Basic Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/sparkline

Demonstrates a basic Textual Sparkline widget. It takes numerical data and displays it visually. The width of the sparkline and the number of data points determine how the data is chunked into bars. The 'summary_function' (here, 'max') dictates the height of each bar based on the data within its chunk. CSS is used to set the width of the sparkline.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Sparkline

data = [1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 4, 3, 1, 1, 8, 8, 2]


class SparklineBasicApp(App[None]):
    CSS_PATH = "sparkline_basic.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Sparkline(
            data,
            summary_function=max,
        )


app = SparklineBasicApp()
if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()

```

```css
Screen {
    align: center middle;
}

Sparkline {
    width: 3;
    margin: 2;
}


```

