--------------------------------

### Textualize IO - Document Manipulation

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

Provides methods for manipulating document content, including getting lines, preparing queries, querying syntax trees, and replacing text ranges.

```APIDOC
## GET /websites/textual_textualize_io/document/get_line

### Description
Retrieves a specific line from the document based on its index.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/document/get_line

### Parameters
#### Query Parameters
- **line_index** (integer) - Required - The index of the line to retrieve.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **line** (string) - The content of the requested line.

### Response Example
{
  "line": "This is the content of the line."
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/document/prepare_query

### Description
Prepares a query for processing.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/document/prepare_query

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **query** (string) - Required - The query string to prepare.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **prepared_query** (object) - The prepared query object.

### Response Example
{
  "prepared_query": {}
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/document/query_syntax_tree

### Description
Queries the syntax tree of the document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/document/query_syntax_tree

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **query** (string) - Required - The query to execute on the syntax tree.
- **start_point** (object) - Optional - The starting point for the query.
- **end_point** (object) - Optional - The ending point for the query.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **syntax_tree_result** (object) - The result of the syntax tree query.

### Response Example
{
  "syntax_tree_result": {}
}

## POST /websites/textualize_io/document/replace_range

### Description
Replaces a specified range of text within the document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textualize_io/document/replace_range

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **start** (object) - Required - The starting position of the range to replace.
- **end** (object) - Required - The ending position of the range to replace.
- **text** (string) - Required - The new text to insert.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **success** (boolean) - Indicates if the replacement was successful.

### Response Example
{
  "success": true
}
```

