### Run Textual App Inline

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/app

Demonstrates how to run a Textual application in inline mode by passing `inline=True` to the `app.run()` method. Inline mode allows the app to appear directly below the prompt without taking over the full terminal, which is useful for terminal-based tools. Note that inline mode is not supported on Windows.

```python
from textual.app import App


class MyApp(App):
    pass


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = MyApp()
    app.run(inline=True)

```

