### App switch_screen(screen)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Switches to a different screen by replacing the top of the screen stack with a new screen.

```APIDOC
## switch_screen(screen)

### Description
Switch to another screen by replacing the top of the screen stack with a new screen.

### Method
`switch_screen(screen)`

### Endpoint
N/A (Method within a class)

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
- **screen** (Screen | str) - Required - Either a Screen object or screen name (the `name` argument when installed).

### Request Example
```python
app.switch_screen("my_screen")
# or
my_screen_object = Screen()
app.switch_screen(my_screen_object)
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
None

#### Response Example
N/A
```

