### Load Event in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/events

The Load event is sent when the Textual application is running but before it enters application mode. This event is suitable for performing setup tasks that do not require visual elements, such as loading configurations or binding keys.

```python
class Load(Event):
    """Sent when the App is running but _before_ the terminal is in application mode.

    Use this event to run any setup that doesn't require any visuals such as
    loading configuration and binding keys.

    * Bubbles
    * Verbose

    """
    pass
```

