### Set Custom Return Code on App Exit (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/app

This example shows how to exit a Textual app with a specific integer return code using the `return_code` parameter of `self.exit()`. This allows differentiation of error conditions from unhandled exceptions. The return code can be accessed via `app.return_code`.

```python
if critical_error:
    self.exit(return_code=4, message="Critical error occurred")
