### Deliver Binary File (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Delivers a binary file to the end-user, either by saving it to a specified directory or initiating a download. This function handles file paths or file-like objects, with options for custom save locations, filenames, open methods (download or browser), MIME types, and a user-defined name. It returns a delivery key upon completion and operates asynchronously in a web browser environment.

```python
deliver_binary(
    path_or_file,
    *,
    save_directory=None,
    save_filename=None,
    open_method="download",
    mime_type=None,
    name=None
)
```

