### Syntax Highlighting Styles in TextAreaTheme (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

This Python code illustrates how to define syntax highlighting styles within a Textual TextAreaTheme. It maps highlight names obtained from tree-sitter queries (like 'heading' and 'link') to specific Rich Style objects, defining their color and other visual properties. This example is part of the 'Monokai' theme configuration.

```python
TextAreaTheme(
    name="monokai",
    base_style=Style(color="#f8f8f2", bgcolor="#272822"),
    gutter_style=Style(color="#90908a", bgcolor="#272822"),
    # ...
    syntax_styles={
        # Colorise @heading and make them bold
        "heading": Style(color="#F92672", bold=True),
        # Colorise and underline @link
        "link": Style(color="#66D9EF", underline=True),
        # ...
    },
)

```

