### Setting min-width in Textual CSS

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/min_width

Illustrates how to apply the `min-width` style within Textual's CSS. It shows examples of setting minimum widths using unitless numbers (representing rows) and viewport-relative units (like `vw`).

```css
/* Set the minimum width to 10 rows */
min-width: 10;

/* Set the minimum width to 25% of the viewport width */
min-width: 25vw;


```

