### Python: Set Grid Rows and Columns with Mixed Units

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/layout

Illustrates setting both grid column widths using fractional units and row heights using percentage units in Textual. This example creates a 3-column grid with specific row heights.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static


class GridLayoutExample(App):
    CSS_PATH = "grid_layout4_row_col_adjust.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static("One", classes="box")
        yield Static("Two", classes="box")
        yield Static("Three", classes="box")
        yield Static("Four", classes="box")
        yield Static("Five", classes="box")
        yield Static("Six", classes="box")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = GridLayoutExample()
    app.run()


```

```tcss
Screen {
    layout: grid;
    grid-size: 3;
    grid-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr;
    grid-rows: 25% 75%;
}

.box {
    height: 100%;
    border: solid green;
}


```

