### Run Test (Async Context Manager)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Provides an asynchronous context manager for testing Textual apps in headless mode. Allows driving the app via a Pilot object for automated testing.

```APIDOC
## async with app.run_test() as pilot:

### Description
An asynchronous context manager for testing apps in headless mode (no output or input). Use this to drive the app via a Pilot object.

### Method
Async Context Manager

### Endpoint
N/A (Context Manager)

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
None

### Request Example
```python
async with app.run_test() as pilot:
    await pilot.click("#Button.ok")
    assert ...
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
N/A (Context Manager provides Pilot object)

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "pilot_object": "<Pilot object for app interaction>"
}
```

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
None

### Request Example
```python
async with app.run_test() as pilot:
    await pilot.click("#Button.ok")
    assert ...
```

