### Select Line by Index in Textualize IO

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

Selects all text within a specific line, identified by its index (starting from 0). This is useful for operations that need to target an entire line of text.

```python
select_line(index)
```

--------------------------------

### Textual Message Handler with Multiple Selectors

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/logger

Demonstrates advanced usage of the '@on' decorator in Textual for message handling. This example targets the activation of a tab within a specific TabbedContent widget, matching both the pane and the widget itself.

```python
# Handle the activation of the tab "#home" within the `TabbedContent` "#tabs".
@on(TabbedContent.TabActivated, "#tabs", pane="#home")
def switch_to_home(self) -> None:
    self.log("Switching back to the home tab.")
    ...

```

--------------------------------

### Get App Return Value (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/app

Retrieves the return value set when the `exit` method is called on the application. Returns None if the return value has not yet been set. This is a property.

```python
return_value
```

