### Apply 'on' Decorator with Arbitrary Attribute Selectors

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/events

Shows how to use the '@on' decorator with keyword arguments to match messages based on arbitrary attributes, beyond standard CSS selectors. This example filters 'TabbedContent.TabActivated' messages by a specific pane ID.

```python
@on(TabbedContent.TabActivated, pane="#home")
def home_tab(self) -> None:
    self.log("Switched back to home tab.")
    ...

```

