### CSS for Reactive Layout in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/reactivity

This CSS file styles the widgets used in the Textual layout example. It sets the input to dock at the top and applies a heavy border to the Name widget, ensuring it can automatically adjust its width and height as intended by the layout=True reactive attribute.

```css
Input {
    dock: top;
    margin-top: 1;
}

Name {
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    border: heavy $secondary;
}


```

--------------------------------

### Embed Actions in Markup Links

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/actions

Illustrates embedding action strings directly into markup using the `@click` tag. Clicking the 'Red', 'Green', or 'Blue' links triggers the `set_background` action with the corresponding color argument. This example utilizes Textual's App, ComposeResult, and Static widgets.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static

TEXT = """
[b]Set your background[/b]
[@click=app.set_background('red')]Red[/]
[@click=app.set_background('green')]Green[/]
[@click=app.set_background('blue')]Blue[/]
"""


class ActionsApp(App):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static(TEXT)

    def action_set_background(self, color: str) -> None:
        self.screen.styles.background = color


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ActionsApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### Get Cursor Left Location - Python

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

Retrieves the location the cursor will move to when moving left. This function takes no arguments and returns a Location object representing the new cursor position.

```Python
get_cursor_left_location()
```

