### Get Row Data by Index

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/data_table

Retrieves all cell values from a row based on its current position (index) in the table. Returns a list of cell values. Raises RowDoesNotExist if the index is out of bounds.

```python
get_row_at(row_index: int) -> list[CellType]
```

