###  !important Rule in Textual CSS

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/CSS

Overrides all specificity rules, forcing a style to be applied. Use sparingly as it can complicate styling. Example: ensure buttons are blue when hovered.

```textualcss
Button:hover {
  background: blue !important;
}
```

