### Add Custom System Command to Textual App

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/command_palette

This Python code demonstrates how to add a custom system command to a Textual application. It extends the base App class and implements the get_system_commands method to yield a new SystemCommand object. This command, when selected, will execute the app's bell method. Ensure Textual is installed for this code to run.

```python
from typing import Iterable

from textual.app import App, SystemCommand
from textual.screen import Screen


class BellCommandApp(App):
    """An app with a 'bell' command."""

    def get_system_commands(self, screen: Screen) -> Iterable[SystemCommand]:
        yield from super().get_system_commands(screen)
        yield SystemCommand("Bell", "Ring the bell", self.bell)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = BellCommandApp()
    app.run()

```

