Source: https://textual.textualize.io/api/scroll_view

Refreshes a range of lines within the ScrollView, starting from a specified vertical coordinate and for a given count. This allows for batch updates to multiple lines.

```python
refresh_lines(y_start, line_count=1)
```

--------------------------------

### Textual App with link-background-hover Example

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/links/link_background_hover

This Python code defines a Textual application that showcases the link-background-hover style. It includes various labels with both regular hyperlinks and Textual action links to demonstrate how the style selectively applies. The application uses a separate CSS file (link_background_hover.tcss) to define the styling rules.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Label


class LinkHoverBackgroundApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "link_background_hover.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Label(
            "Visit the [link='https://textualize.io']Textualize[/link] website.",
            id="lbl1",
        )
        yield Label(
            "Click [@click=app.bell]here[/] for the bell sound.",
            id="lbl2",
        )
        yield Label(
            "You can also click [@click=app.bell]here[/] for the bell sound.",
            id="lbl3",
        )
        yield Label(
            "[@click=app.quit]Exit this application.[/]",
            id="lbl4",
        )


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = LinkHoverBackgroundApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### Textualize Background Style: Basic Usage (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/background

Demonstrates basic usage of the `background` style in Textualize IO by applying different background colors (named, RGB, HSL) to three Label widgets.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Label


class BackgroundApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "background.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Label("Widget 1", id="static1")
        yield Label("Widget 2", id="static2")
        yield Label("Widget 3", id="static3")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = BackgroundApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### All Widget Alignments in Textual (Python & CSS)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/align

Illustrates all possible combinations of horizontal and vertical alignment for widgets within a grid layout. This example showcases Textual's flexible alignment capabilities using Python and CSS.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Container
from textual.widgets import Label


class AlignAllApp(App):
    """App that illustrates all alignments."""

    CSS_PATH = "align_all.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Container(Label("left top"), id="left-top")
        yield Container(Label("center top"), id="center-top")
        yield Container(Label("right top"), id="right-top")
        yield Container(Label("left middle"), id="left-middle")
        yield Container(Label("center middle"), id="center-middle")
        yield Container(Label("right middle"), id="right-middle")
        yield Container(Label("left bottom"), id="left-bottom")
        yield Container(Label("center bottom"), id="center-bottom")
        yield Container(Label("right bottom"), id="right-bottom")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    AlignAllApp().run()


```

```css
#left-top {
    /* align: left top; this is the default value and is implied. */
}

#center-top {
    align: center top;
}

#right-top {
    align: right top;
}

#left-middle {
    align: left middle;
}

#center-middle {
    align: center middle;
}

#right-middle {
    align: right middle;
}

#left-bottom {
    align: left bottom;
}

#center-bottom {
    align: center bottom;
}

#right-bottom {
    align: right bottom;
}

Screen {
    layout: grid;
    grid-size: 3 3;
    grid-gutter: 1;
}

Container {
    background: $boost;
    border: solid gray;
    height: 100%;
}

Label {
    width: auto;
    height: 1;
    background: $accent;
}


```

