### Textual CSS Styling for Widgets

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/CSS

Provides an example of a Textual CSS file (`.tcss`) that styles various widgets within an application. It uses ID selectors (`#dialog`), type selectors (`Button`, `Static`), and class selectors (`.question`, `.buttons`) to define layout and appearance.

```css
/* The top level dialog (a Container) */
#dialog {
    height: 100%;
    margin: 4 8;
    background: $panel;
    color: $text;
    border: tall $background;
    padding: 1 2;
}

/* The button class */
Button {
    width: 1fr;
}

/* Matches the question text */
.question {
    text-style: bold;
    height: 100%;
    content-align: center middle;
}

/* Matches the button container */
.buttons {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    dock: bottom;
}


```

