def get_focusable_widget_at(x, y):
    """
    Get the focusable widget under a given coordinate.
    If the widget directly under the given coordinate is not focusable, then this method will check if any of the ancestors are focusable. If no ancestors are focusable, then `None` will be returned.
    """
    pass
```

--------------------------------

### Python: Multiple Horizontal containers dividing screen space

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/how-to/work-with-containers

Illustrates how multiple Horizontal containers divide the available screen space. Each Horizontal container consumes remaining space, and adding more containers partitions the space further. This example builds upon the previous one by adding a second set of boxes within another Horizontal container.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.containers import Horizontal
from textual.widgets import Placeholder


class Box(Placeholder):
    """Example widget."""

    DEFAULT_CSS = """
    Box {
        width: 16;
        height: 8;
    }
    """


class ContainerApp(App):
    """Simple app to play with containers."""

    CSS = """
    .with-border {
        border: heavy green;
    }
    """

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        with Horizontal(classes="with-border"):
            yield Box()
            yield Box()
            yield Box()
        with Horizontal(classes="with-border"):
            yield Box()
            yield Box()
            yield Box()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = ContainerApp()
    app.run()

```

--------------------------------

### TextArea Widget Parameters

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

This section details the configurable parameters for the TextArea widget, including their types, descriptions, and default values.

```APIDOC
## Parameters

### Path Parameters
None

### Query Parameters
None

### Request Body
None

## TextArea Widget Parameters

- **text** (str) - The initial text to load into the TextArea. Default: `''`
- **language** (str | None) - The language to use. Default: `None`
- **theme** (str) - The theme to use. Default: `'css'`
- **soft_wrap** (bool) - Enable soft wrapping. Default: `True`
- **tab_behavior** (Literal['focus', 'indent']) - If 'focus', pressing tab will switch focus. If 'indent', pressing tab will insert a tab. Default: `'focus'`
- **read_only** (bool) - Enable read-only mode. This prevents edits using the keyboard. Default: `False`
- **show_cursor** (bool) - Show the cursor in read only mode (no effect otherwise). Default: `True`
- **show_line_numbers** (bool) - Show line numbers on the left edge. Default: `False`
- **line_number_start** (int) - What line number to start on. Default: `1`
- **max_checkpoints** (int) - The maximum number of undo history checkpoints to retain. Default: `50`
- **name** (str | None) - The name of the `TextArea` widget. Default: `None`
- **id** (str | None) - The ID of the widget, used to refer to it from Textual CSS. Default: `None`
- **classes** (str | None) - One or more Textual CSS compatible class names separated by spaces. Default: `None`
- **disabled** (bool) - True if the widget is disabled. Default: `False`
- **tooltip** (RenderableType | None) - Optional tooltip. Default: `None`
- **compact** (bool) - Enable compact style (without borders). Default: `False`
- **highlight_cursor_line** (bool) - Highlight the line under the cursor. Default: `True`
- **placeholder** (str | Content) - Text to display when there is not content. Default: `''`
```

