### Select Methods

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/select

Reference for the methods available on the Select widget, including actions and utility functions.

```APIDOC
## Select Methods

### `action_show_overlay()`

- **Description**: Show the overlay.
- **Method**: Any

### `clear()`

- **Description**: Clear the selection if `allow_blank` is `True`. Raises `InvalidSelectValueError` if `allow_blank` is `False`.
- **Method**: Any

### `from_values()` (classmethod)

- **Description**: Initialize the Select control with values specified by an arbitrary iterable. The options shown in the control are computed by calling the built-in `str` on each value.

#### Parameters
- **`values`** (Iterable[SelectType]): Values used to generate options to select from. (Required)
- **`prompt`** (str): Text to show in the control when no option is selected. (Default: `'Select'`)
- **`allow_blank`** (bool): Enables or disables the ability to have the widget in a state with no selection made. (Default: `True`)
- **`value`** (SelectType | NoSelection): Initial value selected. Should be one of the values in `values`. (Default: `BLANK`)
- **`type_to_search`** (bool): If `True`, typing will search for options. (Default: `True`)
- **`name`** (str | None): The name of the select control. (Default: `None`)
- **`id`** (str | None): The ID of the control in the DOM. (Default: `None`)
- **`classes`** (str | None): The CSS classes of the control. (Default: `None`)
- **`disabled`** (bool): Whether the control is disabled or not. (Default: `False`)
- **`compact`** (bool): Enable compact style? (Default: `False`)

#### Returns
- **`Select[SelectType]`**: A new Select widget with the provided values as options.
- **Method**: classmethod

### `is_blank()`

- **Description**: Indicates whether this `Select` is blank or not.

#### Returns
- **`bool`**: True if the selection is blank, False otherwise.
- **Method**: Any

### `set_options()`

- **Description**: Set the options for the Select. This will reset the selection. The selection will be empty, if allowed, otherwise the first valid option is picked. Raises `EmptySelectError` if the options iterable is empty and `allow_blank` is `False`.

#### Parameters
- **`options`** (Iterable[tuple[RenderableType, SelectType]]): An iterable of tuples containing the renderable to display for each option and the corresponding internal value. (Required)
- **Method**: Any
```

