### Basic Widget Alignment with Textual (Python & CSS)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/align

Demonstrates basic centering of child labels within an app using the 'align: center middle;' CSS property. This example requires a Python script and a corresponding CSS file.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Label


class AlignApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "align.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Label("Vertical alignment with [b]Textual[/]", classes="box")
        yield Label("Take note, browsers.", classes="box")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = AlignApp()
    app.run()

```

```css
Screen {
    align: center middle;
}

.box {
    width: 40;
    height: 5;
    margin: 1;
    padding: 1;
    background: green;
    color: white 90%;
    border: heavy white;
}


```

