### Create Basic DirectoryTree - Python

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/directory_tree

Demonstrates how to create a simple DirectoryTree widget that displays the contents of the current working directory. This requires the textual library and basic App structure.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import DirectoryTree


class DirectoryTreeApp(App):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield DirectoryTree("./")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = DirectoryTreeApp()
    app.run()

```

