### Document Navigator Methods

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/widgets/text_area

APIs for navigating through document lines and positions.

```APIDOC
## POST /websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/clamp_reachable

### Description
Clamps a location to be reachable within the document.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/clamp_reachable

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **location** (object) - Required - The location to clamp. (See `Location` object structure).

### Request Example
```json
{
  "location": {"line": 20, "column": 10}
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **location** (object) - The clamped location. (See `Location` object structure).

## POST /websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/get_location_above

### Description
Gets the location directly above the given location.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/get_location_above

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **location** (object) - Required - The starting location. (See `Location` object structure).

### Request Example
```json
{
  "location": {"line": 15, "column": 7}
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **location** (object) - The location above. (See `Location` object structure).

## POST /websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/get_location_at_y_offset

### Description
Gets the location at a specific vertical offset from a starting location.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/websites/textual_textualize_io/document_navigator/get_location_at_y_offset

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **location** (object) - Required - The starting location. (See `Location` object structure).
- **vertical_offset** (integer) - Required - The vertical offset in lines.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "location": {"line": 10, "column": 3},
  "vertical_offset": 5
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **location** (object) - The location at the specified offset. (See `Location` object structure).

