### Basic Margin Example with Label in Python and CSS

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/margin

Demonstrates how to apply margin to a Label widget using CSS. The `margin: 4 8;` in the CSS file sets a top/bottom margin of 4 units and a left/right margin of 8 units. The Python code sets up a basic Textual app with a Label.

```python
from textual.app import App
from textual.widgets import Label

TEXT = """I must not fear.
Fear is the mind-killer.
Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration.
I will face my fear.
I will permit it to pass over me and through me.
And when it has gone past, I will turn the inner eye to see its path.
Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain."


class MarginApp(App):
    CSS_PATH = "margin.tcss"

    def compose(self):
        yield Label(TEXT)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = MarginApp()
    app.run()

```

```css
Screen {
    background: white;
    color: black;
}

Label {
    margin: 4 8;
    background: blue 20%;
    border: blue wide;
    width: 100%;
}


```

--------------------------------

### Control Widget Content Area Size with Box Sizing (Python)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/styles

Demonstrates the 'box-sizing' style in Textual. 'border-box' (default) includes padding and border in the widget's total dimensions, while 'content-box' adds them, expanding the widget's size. This example shows two Static widgets with identical dimensions and borders, but different box-sizing values, highlighting the impact on content area size.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static


TEXT = """I must not fear.
Fear is the mind-killer.
Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration.
I will face my fear.
I will permit it to pass over me and through me.
And when it has gone past, I will turn the inner eye to see its path.
Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain.
"""


class BoxSizing(App):
    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        self.widget1 = Static(TEXT)
        yield self.widget1
        self.widget2 = Static(TEXT)
        yield self.widget2

    def on_mount(self) -> None:
        self.widget1.styles.background = "purple"
        self.widget2.styles.background = "darkgreen"
        self.widget1.styles.width = 30
        self.widget2.styles.width = 30
        self.widget1.styles.height = 6
        self.widget2.styles.height = 6
        self.widget1.styles.border = ("heavy", "white")
        self.widget2.styles.border = ("heavy", "white")
        self.widget1.styles.padding = 1
        self.widget2.styles.padding = 1
        self.widget2.styles.box_sizing = "content-box"


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = BoxSizing()
    app.run()

```

