### Textual CSS Styling Rules

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/tutorial

This Textual CSS (tcss) file defines styles for various widgets within the application. It includes rules for the general Stopwatch container, TimeDisplay widgets, Buttons, and specific elements identified by IDs like `#start`, `#stop`, and `#reset`.

```css
Stopwatch {
    background: $boost;
    height: 5;
    margin: 1;
    min-width: 50;
    padding: 1;
}

TimeDisplay {
    text-align: center;
    color: $foreground-muted;
    height: 3;
}

Button {
    width: 16;
}

#start {
    dock: left;
}

#stop {
    dock: left;
    display: none;
}

#reset {
    dock: right;
}
```

