### Horizontal Layout with Scrolling in Textual

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/guide/layout

Illustrates how to enable horizontal scrolling in a Textual application when widgets exceed the available screen width. This is achieved by setting `overflow-x: auto;` in the CSS. This example requires the `textual` library.

```python
from textual.app import App, ComposeResult
from textual.widgets import Static


class HorizontalLayoutExample(App):
    CSS_PATH = "horizontal_layout_overflow.tcss"

    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:
        yield Static("One", classes="box")
        yield Static("Two", classes="box")
        yield Static("Three", classes="box")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app = HorizontalLayoutExample()
    app.run()

```

```css
Screen {
    layout: horizontal;
    overflow-x: auto;
}

.box {
    height: 100%;
    border: solid green;
}

```

