### Define Grid Columns Width (Textual CSS)

Source: https://textual.textualize.io/styles/grid/grid_columns

This CSS snippet demonstrates how to set the width of grid columns using the `grid-columns` property in Textual. It shows examples for setting all columns to a percentage width and for creating columns with relative widths.

```textualcss
/* Set all columns to have 50% width */
grid-columns: 50%;

/* Every other column is twice as wide as the first one */
grid-columns: 1fr 2fr;
```

